<section id="faq">
  <div class="container">
   <div class="faq-wrap fade-in">

    <div class="faq-group">
      <h2>Getting started</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>How do I register?</h3><p>Register a team of 1–6 at <a href="register.html">register.html</a> (中文: <a href="zh/register.html">/zh/register.html</a>). Member 1 is the point of contact and receives all team email.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is there an entry fee?</h3><p>No — participation is free.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I compete solo, or do I form my own team?</h3><p>Teams are 1–6 people; solo is allowed, and you form your own team. Looking for teammates? Use our <a href="https://discord.gg/pGwRbMRjuH" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a> (and the <a href="https://qr61.cn/oioUKl/qtksKk2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shanghai testbed WeChat group</a> for participants in China).</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What experience level is required?</h3><p>All levels are welcome — we provide baseline examples and tutorials.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group">
      <h2>The competition</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What are the tasks?</h3><p>Three independent tracks — Task 1: Cable Routing &amp; Plugging; Task 2: Deformable Material Handling (Thermal Pad Placement); Task 3: Assisted Living &amp; Feeding. Enter one or more; each is ranked independently.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Which simulators are used?</h3><p>NVIDIA Isaac Sim and MuJoCo. The MuJoCo version of Task 2 is not in the release (deformable-object fidelity isn't ready yet); if you build your own, it still counts.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What teleoperation interfaces are provided?</h3><p>To facilitate data collection, the Teleoperation Toolkit provides Franka Duo GELLO (<a href="https://franka.de/de/gello" target="_blank" rel="noopener">franka.de/de/gello</a>), Keyboard Control, Foot Pedal Control, and VR Control.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Do I need to travel?</h3><p>The challenge is primarily simulation-based — the open simulation benchmark runs through an open call and needs no travel. Teams that advance from simulation reach real-world validation on Mobile FR3 Duo robots at partner labs in Hamburg, Munich, Pittsburgh, and Shanghai, structured in two windows: a hands-on bench-testing window on the real platform for qualifying teams (Aug 10 – Aug 19, 2026), then an organizer-run window (Aug 20 – Aug 31, 2026) in which teams keep submitting code while the organizers run all real-robot bench testing and evaluation for cross-site comparability.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>When are the simulation packages and baselines released?</h3><p>The first public release is expected within 3–5 days: simulation environments, the Teleoperation Toolkit, benchmark documentation, and baseline examples.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>How will submissions be evaluated?</h3><p>The official rulebook and evaluation metrics are released together with the benchmark package; submission instructions follow.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group">
      <h2>Compute</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What compute can I get, and how do I apply?</h3><p>Three grant programs, open now at <a href="compute-apply.html">compute-apply.html</a> — Google Cloud (up to US$1,000 of A100; usage Jul 15–20, apply by ~Jul 8), Computational Freedom (40 h RTX 4090 or 25 h L40S; mainland-China-based teams; needs a mainland-China IP and phone number), and AMD Instinct MI300X (shared 8× MI300X in Taipei, all teams). Note: Google Cloud is generally unreachable from mainland China without a VPN — mainland teams should use Computational Freedom or MI300X.</p></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Do I need my own GPU?</h3><p>Not necessarily — the grants above are intended to cover compute needs.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group">
      <h2>AMD Solution Award</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>What is the AMD Solution Award?</h3><p>A per-task prize for the Top 3 teams that complete the full AI workflow — data processing, training, inference, and official evaluation — on the AMD ROCm ecosystem, verified via your Docker image and the official AMD evaluation environment. It's optional and doesn't affect the overall ranking.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-group">
      <h2>Stay connected</h2>
      <div class="faq-item"><h3>Where do I get help and updates?</h3><p><a href="https://discord.gg/pGwRbMRjuH" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a>, the <a href="index.html">website</a>, and the <a href="https://qr61.cn/oioUKl/qtksKk2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WeChat group</a> for participants in China.</p></div>
    </div>

   </div>
  </div>
</section>
